@startuml state-requirement
!theme plain

title Power Atlas -- Requirement Pipeline State Machine
caption Lifecycle states for client requirement submissions through admin review

skinparam stateBorderColor #555555
skinparam stateBackgroundColor #E8F4FD
skinparam stateArrowColor #444444
skinparam noteBorderColor #888888

[*] --> new_submission : "Client submits\nrequirement via\npublic form"

state new_submission : Requirement just received.
state new_submission : Confirmation email sent to client.
state new_submission : Notification created for admins.
state new_submission : Requirement code assigned (REQ-YYYY-NNNNN).

state admin_review : Admin is reviewing the requirement.
state admin_review : Admin can view all details.
state admin_review : Admin decides next action.

state approved : Requirement has been approved.
state approved : Client notified via email.
state approved : Ready for engineering team.

state rejected : Requirement has been rejected.
state rejected : Client notified with reason.
state rejected : No further action needed.

state client_edit : Changes requested by admin.
state client_edit : Client notified to revise.
state client_edit : Client can update and resubmit.

state implemented : Linked to an active project.
state implemented : Engineering work in progress.
state implemented : Terminal state.

new_submission --> admin_review : "Auto-routed to\nadmin queue"

admin_review --> approved : "Admin approves\nrequirement"
admin_review --> rejected : "Admin rejects\nrequirement\n(with reason)"
admin_review --> client_edit : "Admin requests\nchanges from client"

client_edit --> admin_review : "Client resubmits\nupdated requirement"

approved --> implemented : "Requirement linked\nto a project by\nengineer"

rejected --> [*] : "Terminal state\n(no further action)"
implemented --> [*] : "Terminal state\n(project handles\nfrom here)"

note right of new_submission
  **Entry point:** Public form at
  /requirements/submit
  No authentication required.
  Requirement code generated
  automatically.
end note

note right of admin_review
  **Decision point:** Admin can take
  one of three actions:
  1. Approve (move forward)
  2. Reject (close with reason)
  3. Request edits (send back to client)

  All transitions are logged in
  **requirement_changes** table.
end note

note left of client_edit
  Client receives email with
  admin's feedback. Can edit
  and resubmit, which returns
  the requirement to admin_review.
end note

note bottom of approved
  Email notification sent to client.
  Notifications created for engineers.
  requirement_changes entry logged
  with old/new values.
end note

note bottom of implemented
  The requirement is now tracked
  as part of a project. Further
  status is managed via the
  **project** lifecycle.
end note

@enduml
